## 6. Views & Business Logic

- CBVs for non-trivial logic, FBVs for simple endpoints
- Views must stay thin — delegate to `services.py` / `selectors.py`
- `services.py` — write/mutation logic
- `selectors.py` — read/query logic
- `tasks.py` — async/background work (Celery or Django-Q)
- Login failure → redirect to **homepage** (not a blank error)
- After successful registration → skip email confirmation → redirect to **profile page**
  with page title **"Complete your profile"**
- Unauthenticated access to protected pages → redirect to **login page**

### Profile Completion Gate (middleware)

Implement `ProfileCompleteMiddleware` in `apps/users/middleware.py`.
It runs on every request **after** `AuthenticationMiddleware`.

Rules:
- Only applies to **authenticated** users
- A profile is considered **incomplete** if `UserProfile.profile_completed_at` is `None`
  - Add `profile_completed_at = models.DateTimeField(null=True, blank=True)` to `UserProfile`
  - Set it to `now()` on the first successful save of the profile form
- If the profile is incomplete, redirect to `/profile/?next=<original_url>` with
  page title **"Complete your profile"** — regardless of which protected URL was requested
- Exempt URLs (never redirected, even when profile is incomplete):
  - `/profile/` itself
  - `/logout/`
  - `/health/`
  - Any URL matching `settings.PROFILE_GATE_EXEMPT_URLS` (a list, configurable in `base.py`)
- Public pages (unauthenticated access allowed) are unaffected — the gate only
  triggers for authenticated users with an incomplete profile
- After the profile form is submitted and saved successfully for the first time,
  set `profile_completed_at = now()` and redirect to `next` param (or `/dashboard/`)

